  m_Name: Forest-Howl
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  storyText: "\"Please, just point me in the direction of my friend's cabin,\" you
    say and give him the address.\r\n\"Suit yourself,\" the old man says and finds
    a map. With a pencil, he marks the route to your friends house and hands it to
    you. \"Now, get outta here. And don't look\u2013\"\r\n\"Don't look up. Yeah,
    I got it,\" you say and exit the way you came. As you're walking down the porch
    steps, the old man calls after you.\r\n\"I'd be careful if I were you. Tonight's
    a full moon. Stick to the path.\"\r\n\"Yeah, sure. Thanks,\" you say and continue
    walking. With some distance between you and the old man's cabin, you begin to
    feel a little better despite the dark. And although the old man was a little
    on the wild side, his directions on the map seem pretty clear, and you feel confident
    you'll make it to your friends place any minute now.\r\nBut then you hear a howl,
    and it sounds awfully close. You pick up the pace and hope that it's just a fox
    or coyote, but by the sound of it, that doesn't seem likely. Suddenly, there's
    a bad feeling in the pit of your stomach, and you freeze. You look down at your
    feet and see that the path has vanished. You must have accidentally wandered
    off of it. And now there's something really big running through the trees, and
    it sounds like it's fast and coming right toward you. You realize that running
    is futile. There are only two options...."
